The '''2015 Heiwadai Bowl''' is a [[college football]] [[bowl game]] that was played on Sunday, November 1, 2015 at Heiwadai Athletics Stadium in [[Japan]]. [[Seinan Gakuin University]] representing the [[Kyūshū Collegiate American Football Association]] and [[Hiroshima University]] representing the [[Chushikoku Collegiate American Football Association]]. Seinan Gakuin beat Hiroshima by a score of 17-7.<ref>{{cite web|title=KCAFA 2015 schedule results |publisher=Kyushu American Football Association|url=http://www.kcafa.jp/home/result.html#GA-28|accessdate=November 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Heiwadai Bowl Stats |publisher=Kyushu American Football Association|url=http://www.kcafa.jp/data/2015a/stats/GA-28.pdf|accessdate=November 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=hushikoku Collegiate American Football Association Blog |publisher=Chushikoku Collegiate American Football Association|url=http://cscaa.seesaa.net/|accessdate=November 2, 2015}}</ref>
