{{Infobox stadium | stadium_name = Kohtla-Järve Spordikeskuse staadion | image = | location = [[Kohtla-Järve]], [[Estonia]] | broke_ground = | opened = | renovated = | closed = | demolished = | owner = Kohtla-Järve Spordikeskus | operator = | surface = Grass<ref name="stadium">{{cite web | title=EOK - Spordirajatised — KOHTLA-JÄRVE SPORDIKESKUS | url=http://www.eok.ee/spordirajatised?view=spordiklubid&type=1&id=404&sport_filt=&vars=3 | deadurl=yes | archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110717135647/http://www.eok.ee/spordirajatised?view=spordiklubid&type=1&id=404&sport_filt=&vars=3 | archivedate=2011-07-17 | df= }}{{et icon}}</ref> | construction_cost = | architect = | former_names = | tenants = <center>[[FC Lootus Kohtla-Järve|Lootus Kohtla-Järve]] ([[Meistriliiga]]) | dimensions = 100 x 64 m<ref name="stadium" /> | capacity = 2,200 }}
'''Kohtla-Järve Spordikeskuse staadion''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Kohtla-Järve]], [[Estonia]]. It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches and hosts the matches of [[FC Lootus Kohtla-Järve]]. The stadium holds 2,200 people.
