{{No footnotes|date=March 2012}}
{{for|[[Labrinth]]'s brother|MckNasty}}
'''McNasty''' refers to a style of slam dunk in the American sport [[Slamball]]. The move consists of a player launching himself from the outside [[trampoline]], rotating 360-degrees and putting the ball between their legs before dunking the ball. The move was originated and made popular by [[Slamball]] phenom Sean "inches" Jackson, of the Mob, who used the dunk in the 2002 [[Slamball]] dunk contest. A variation known as the reverse McNasty was also used in the contest.

