{{Infobox sports award | name = Woman of Steel | image = | image_size = | alt = | caption = | sport = [[Rugby league]] | competition = [[Women's Super League (rugby league)|Women's Super League]] | discipline = | givenfor = | english = | localnames = | nickname = | sponsor = | location = | country = England | presenter = | first = 2018 | number = | last = | firstwinner = {{flagicon|ENG|12}} [[Georgia Roche]] ([[Castleford Tigers Women|Castleford Tigers]]) | mostwins = | mostrecent = {{flagicon|ENG|12}} [[Georgia Roche]] ([[Castleford Tigers Women|Castleford Tigers]]) | url = <!-- {{URL|example.com}} --> }}
The '''Woman of Steel''' is an award in English [[rugby league]]. It is awarded to the player of the year in the [[Women's Super League (rugby league)|Women's Super League]]; the winner is determined by a poll of the players in the Women's Super League.
The award was inaugurated in 2018 and the winner will be announced as part of the [[Man of Steel Awards|Steve Prescott Man of Steel Awards]] in October each year.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/rugby-league/45665985 |title=Woman of Steel: Lois Forsell, Tara-Jane Stanley and Georgia Roche on shortlist |work=[[BBC Sport]] |date=27 September 2018 |accessdate=27 September 2018}}</ref>
==2018== The inaugural nominees were [[Lois Forsell]] of [[Leeds Rhinos Women]], [[Georgia Roche]] and [[Tara-Jane Stanley]], both of [[Castleford Tigers Women]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.totalrl.com/first-woman-of-steel-shortlist-announced/ |title=First Woman of Steel shortlist announced |publisher=Total RL |date=27 September 2018 |accessdate=27 September 2018}}</ref> The award was won by Georgia Roche.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rugby-league.com/article/53698/ben-barba-named-steve-prescott-man-of-steel |title=All the winners from tonight's Man of Steel Awards Dinner |publisher=Rugby Football League |date=8 October 2018}}</ref>
